Key Match Events: Emilio Nsue scored a hat-trick in the match
Equatorial Guinea achieved a 4-2 victory over Guinea-Bissau
Esteban Orozco scored an own goal for Guinea-Bissau
Franculino Djú missed a penalty for Guinea-Bissau
Josete Miranda scored for Equatorial Guinea
Zé Turbo scored a consolation goal for Guinea-Bissau in stoppage time
Post-Match Reflections: Equatorial Guinea's victory provisionally lifts them above Ivory Coast to the top of Group A
Guinea-Bissau now has it all to do if they want to qualify for the knockout stages
Miscellaneous Highlights: Emilio Nsue's second hat-trick in international football
VAR overturned a penalty for Guinea-Bissau
The match took place at the Alassane Ouattara Olympic Stadium in Ebimpe
The match was part of the Africa Cup of Nations 2024
